profile:
The Home Improvement People have completed literally thousands of renovations since our inception. We are a unique award winning contracting company, consulted by various media as industry experts. 
Please view our website at homeimprovementpeople.com to view images of some of our projects. 
For our clients' convenience, we've implemented progress billing as well as financing.
Regardless of scope, we approach every single home renovation with a foundation of strong design aesthetics, comprehensive product options, sound project management, and a commitment to craftsmanship.
 
Our projects range from remodelled bathrooms and kitchens, to rear additions,  hardwood flooring, basements, second story additions and other extensive renovations. We undertake work in all budget ranges.
 
Choosing a reputable contractor is the most important decision you will make regarding your renovation. From plans and permits, to last little finishing details, The Home Improvement People is committed to completing your renovations and home improvements in a professional manner and to your complete satisfaction.
We take pride in our personalized service and our high quality workmanship. 
Call us for quality, insured work - completed on time, and on budget.
416-782-7605.

profile:
Paint Core Finishes is a custom refinishing company. We provide top-notch kitchen cabinet, vanity, woodwork and furniture re-spraying, refinishing and painting services in the GTA.

Reclaim your kitchen cabinets, vanities, and woodwork!

We believe in doing things right the first time. We specialize in the fine art of cabinet refinishing, painting, re-spraying and wood finishing. If you have a tired looking kitchen and are thinking of replacing it, think twice. We have salvaged hundreds of kitchens with our factory finish process. We pride ourselves on producing high quality finishes on all your existing cabinetry, millwork and furniture. By implementing a very thorough preparation, combined with the right application systems, topnotch equipment and coatings we provide amazing results. This is our recipe for success!

Our philosophy is that a refinished kitchen shouldn’t look refinished; it should look like it was bought that way.

profile:
Since 1973 Olympic Kitchens Inc has been a family run business providing timeless cabinetry for custom dream home builds and home renovation projects.  At the center of these projects is always a stunning kitchen but we bring our expertise and quality to built-ins, bathrooms and specialty millwork. 

Now that you’re thinking about a new kitchen, you certainly want the breathtaking results you may have seen online and in pictures. But a truly beautiful kitchen is more than skin deep. Real value for your investment includes things like classic styling that will stand the test of time. A company that understands and can deliver current trends and advanced products. Flexibility that lets you put your personal stamp on your own kitchen design. Hand crafted cabinets that look as good up close as they do from a distance. Durable surfaces that stand up to repeated cleaning. 
 Functionality that makes things easy to store – and easy to find.

We’re proud to say that Olympic Kitchens Inc. can offer you all these things, and more. We’ve learned a thing or two over 45 years of building custom cabinetry. Most important, we’ve learned that true satisfaction with a kitchen occurs on many levels – and ¬that each level must be addressed right from the beginning to ensure it exceeds expectations. Our clients include custom home builders, architects, interior designers and renovation contractors who understand ﬁne work, and who recommend us to families like yours.

Services Provided
Custom Bathroom Vanities, Custom Cabinet Doors, Custom Cabinets, Custom Kitchen Cabinets, Custom Walk-in Closets, Drafting, Floor Plans, Green Building, Home Additions, Home Extensions, Kitchen Design, Lighting Design, Sustainable Design, Kitchen Remodeling

From the year 1989 Brampton Kitchen & Cabinets Ltd. has been designing and manufacturing Custom Cabinetry, with Custom Kitchens being its flagship service. Brampton Kitchen follows a set of ethical values and professional procedures. We operate with the highest level of integrity and rigidly adhere to the policy of customer service, accountability and skill. We are a credible organization that stands behind its product. 
Extensive experience of several years and expertise of best artisans and craftsmen, we create designs that stand out. We can turn your dream into reality without having to compromise on budget or quality.

profile:
Welcome to NewKitchenToronto ! Ikea kitchens are beautiful and inexpensive. But do you find it difficult not only selecting all the components but also designing and fitting the kitchen to your space? <b>We specialize in custom Ikea kitchens!

***
 
We will work with you to design your project, help you choose which components to buy and also custom fit everything to your space. We are faster and less expensive than Ikea's installers, and we give you that personalized custom service.
 
Customer satisfaction is our top priority. Let's work together to get you that <b>beautiful new kitchen for less money than you ever thought possible.
 
With our 25 years of experience and hundreds of satisfied customers in the Toronto and Greater Toronto Area, we can guarantee, you will be completely satisfied with our honesty, customer service, quality, and prices.
 
In addition to custom Ikea kitchens we offer complete services for:
 
    * Custom Made Kitchens Cupboards,
    * Kitchens Cabinets Re-facing and Remodeling
    * Countertops Replacement
    * Bathroom Vanity Cabinets
    * Walk-in Closet Organizers
    * Laundry Room Organizer Cabinets
    * Bars and Entertainment Center Units
    * Home Office and Library Cabinets
    * Commercial projects
    * Design & Consultation
    * Drywall
    * Complete Renovations
 
About Us:

Dmitriy Rozenberg is the General Manager at New Kitchen Toronto. He began his career as a quality home renovator in 1986 after graduating from university as a Civil Engineer.
In 1987 he began making custom cabinets and doing his own millwork for his projects.
From 1991 he was specializing exclusively on custom cabinetry and woodworking.
Under his supervision New Kitchen Toronto designs, manufactures and installs cabinets with exceptional quality and highest attention to details.

***

We at New Kitchen Toronto use a wide variety of Canadian-manufactured cabinets, countertops, components and accessories that, together with our craftsmanship will ensure your complete satisfaction with the project.
We offer any product or service that exists on the woodworking market today at affordable prices.

We are following all health and safety percautions as directed by the Province of Ontario and look forward to speaking with you soon until we can meet in person.


***


At Pulsar Design, every design is the result of our devotion to creating beautiful yet highly functional spaces. Combining our ability to manufacture custom components with a wide range of styles and an unlimited colour selection, we can create custom designs that suit your needs as well as your personal sense of style. Driven by our desire for quality, we pride ourselves on being at the forefront of the cabinetry making industry. In short, Pulsar Design creates sophisticated spaces that cater to each and every individual.

***
HISTORY:

Pulsar Design was established  2001, when Lillian Besevic, an interior designer, wanted to find a company that could create custom cabinetry to her client’s needs and specifications. After working with several firms, she was unable to find a company that could offer flexibility in design in addition to meeting her high standards of quality. 
Soon after, she started Pulsar Design so that she could build what her clients wanted, how they wanted it. Today, Lillian and her partner, Vladimir, run a successful business based on their commitment to providing quality custom cabinetry and outstanding customer service.
***
 STANDARD:
Our standards of excellence are apparent in each stage of the design, production and installation process. We have built our reputation on the ability to consistently satisfy our clients. As a result, we are confident that the quality of our service and craftsmanship will exceed your expectations in the realization of your dream space.
***
PROMISE:
Whether you are building a new home or renovating an existing space, we treat each project with the same amount of care and attention. Our goal is to create sophisticated spaces that will fulfill your every need as well as appeal to your personal sense of style.
***
 WHAT WE DO:

Renovations:
When you choose Pulsar Design to renovate your space, we take care of all the details on your behalf. We coordinate every aspect of the design, manufacturing and installation process, sparing you the hassle and burden of managing the project yourself.
***
New Homes:
When Pulsar Design installs a kitchen into a new home, the work is often carried out under the direction of the homebuilder. As a result, our focus is to integrate with the builder’s schedule and maintain in constant communication so that there aren’t any unnecessary delays.
***
HOW WE DO IT:

1) Visit:  Make an appointment to visit our showroom to talk to our experienced designer.
2) Design:  We will walk you through the decision making process in an easy, comfortable
                  way. You can explore the array of materials, styles, colors and options available
                  to you.
3) Install:  Let Pulsar Design coordinate and manage all the details for you.
4) Enjoy:    Enjoy your dream space for years to come !

FINISHES:

Stained:
§ Wiping Stain: Stain is applied with a cloth, highlighting the natural variations in the color of the wood.

§ Spraying Stain: Stain is applied with a spray gun, giving the wood the most uniform appearance.

· CABINET SPECIFICATIONS:
· Concealed cabinets are constructed out of solid coloured or wood patterned 5/8” thick high-grade 120-gram density scratch-resistant melamine with either PVC or melamine pre-glued edge tape. This includes the sides, tops, bottoms, backs, shelves, drawer bottoms and drawer backs.
· Open cabinets are constructed out of:
o ¾” painted medium density fibreboard to match the exterior of the cabinets.
o ¾” stained maple veneer plywood to match the exterior of the cabinets.
Drawers use BLUM Tandembox full extension metal sliders for smooth uninhibited motion. These slides are integrated with BLUMOTION, a soft closing mechanism, for silent effortless closing every time.
Doors use Hettich fully concealed hinges and have a 110-degree opening angle.
· ACCESSORIES:
o There are many different options when it comes to organizing your space. We carry a broad range of accessories to suit all your organizational needs.

Kakoz Kitchens & Custom Cabinetry is a family owned business with years of experience in kitchen design including creation, installation and remodeling. We are specialized in the production of fine kitchen cabinets, custom shelving, and high-end closet storage solutions . We are confident in the products we make, as well as the services we provide, on every project will suit your vision.

20 years of experience
Our 20 years of experience led to remodeling any kitchen, wall unit, home office, or walk-in closet style you like

Whether meeting with you and your family or collaborating with architects, contractors, and interior decorators, we’re here to help you define your scope of work and articulate a vision that’s uniquely yours.


The experienced design team will turn your vision into a reality detailed plan, creating custom solutions that blend form a function to fit all your family’s needs.

Build
Our designs of combining the old and the new world approach to the top of craftsmanship and that mean you can have the best rich design from both worlds for kitchens or bathrooms. We make every piece of cabinetry in our shop in Toronto, Proudly 100% Canadian-made. Our Values
We believe in building durable and functional cabinetry that will make things easy to store, easy to find, and easy to clean. By choosing to work with us you will get the real value for your investment and your cabinets will look as good up close as they do from a distance.

profile:
With our painter's techniques and attention to detail, we can make your home and/or business look and feel more like your own. 

We are residential and commercial house painters painting in Pickering, Ajax, Scarborough and the greater Toronto area. We also serve the York and Durham regions to as far north as Aurora.

Our house painting services include general painting, plaster repair, wallpaper and wallcovering installation and removal, decorative painting, and faux finishes. We also offer more speciality services listed under the "Service Details" section below. 

Founded by award-winning decorator Walter Schellenberg in 1989, Decorating with a Difference has had the privilege of working in many of the finest homes in all of Toronto and the GTA, and has now expanded locally with the addition of his sons joining the business, and the partnerships he has created over the years. 

If you are interested in working with us to start or complete your project, please contact us and we'll respond as soon as possible, we look forward to working with you!

Note: 
In an effort to respond quicker, we have set up an automated estimate booking system on our website that will allow you the client, to choose the date that works best for you to have your project quote done in person. 

The system instantly confirms the appointment once you select the date so there is no need to wait for a call. That way you don't have to wait around for a reply, and we can keep painting without checking our phone.
products: We work with any brand of paint, varnish, stain, wallpaper or wallcovering that is required for your project. From low VOC paint for clearer air, to oil paint for that tough smooth finish used on doors and kitchen cabinets. We can even install grass cloth or silk wallcoverings.
services: General Painting, Wallpaper/ Wallcovering (installation & removal), Decorative Painting, Plaster Repair, Faux Finishes, & Murals.
brands: We work with Benjamin Moore, Sherwin-Williams, Behr, and Farrow & Ball to name a few.

profile:
Established in 2015, we are a fast growing, full service, detail-oriented custom cabinetry company trusted by customers in the Greater Toronto Area.

Fantasy Kitchen specializes in offering top-quality custom kitchen cabinets in Markham. We are passionate about enhancing the beauty and functionality of your home. As the most trusted cabinet manufacturer in GTA, we craft and install custom bathroom vanities in Richmond Hill.

Our goal is to exceed your expectations on every project, regardless of size. We have a team of skilled craftsmen for designing and installing custom wall units in Markham. Whether you need custom kitchen cabinets, bathroom vanity, walk-in closet, or home bar, we can customize cabinetry to suit your taste, style, and budget. Our team can also install custom wall units in Richmond Hill homes and commercial spaces. As a full-service cabinetry installer, we can make your home more stylish, comfortable, and spacious.

When it comes to kitchen cabinets and bathroom vanities, you need products that can withstand temperature fluctuations due to heat from stoves and ovens and moisture from showers, sinks, and dishwashers.

We focus on using the highest quality material and durable fixtures that can stand the test of time. Our process involves taking accurate measurements and understanding your vision to deliver tailored solutions. When we install custom bathroom vanities in Vaughan, we make sure to provide you a product that complements the size and style of your space.

We strive to turn your bathroom into a sanctuary. When we work on any project, our designers consider aesthetics, as well as functionality. Our experts will not only help you choose the right cabinetry material but can also guide you to select the best hardware and finishes that look phenomenal and can stand up to the challenges of a bathroom or kitchen environment. Our services include:

• Kitchen & Bathroom Design Consultation
• Custom Cabinets Manufacturer
• Kitchen Cabinetry Installation
• Bathroom Vanity Installation
• Walk-In Closet Installation
• Home Bar & Pantry
• And More!

At Fantasy Kitchen, we take great pride in our workmanship. From crafting custom Kitchen cabinets in Markham to installing bathroom vanities in Richmond Hill, we provide a wide range of superior quality products and spectacular installation services for almost every budget and style. We always respect your time and consider your ideas to ensure that the project is completed as per your requirements and expectations. We provide you the freedom to choose from our wide assortment of premium materials. In addition to this, we always provide accurate project quote to keep you informed. The cabinets we install provide a great storage solution to provide you an organized and attractive-looking space.

profile:
Arch Kitchen Cabinets has been manufacturing and installing quality kitchens and bath vanities all over the Greater Toronto Area. Arch Kitchen Cabinets specializes in custom made and refacing kitchens, bathroom vanities, organizers and shelving units explicitly designed to fulfill the needs of individual households. Every kitchen cabinet, vanity and or shelving unit manufactured at Arch Kitchen is one of a kind, because of a client�s unique choice in style and custom design. Every kitchen is designed by hand or by using sophisticated design software, by our qualified personal with over 30 years experience in architectural and interior design. Our expert team of cabinet makers specialize in hand assembling all cabinets to insure the best craftsmanship possible.

Arch Kitchen Cabinets provides service not only in Toronto but also in Scarborough and its neighboring cities Pickering, Mississauga and Markham. Arch Kitchen runs a new production facility capable of overtaking and completing any task in a reasonable period of time. Under the guidance of qualified supervisors with over 35 years of building and architectural experience, Arch Kitchen is able to meet any challenge in the time required. Arch Kitchen specializes in a variety of wood used in the manufacturing of our products such as Pine, Maple, Oak and Cherry. Cabinet doors and countertops offered in a a wide variety of styles, colours and textures allow customers to have many options when deciding upon which will suite their home best. Arch Kitchen also has a carries a wide variety of door finishes for the customer to choose from. Good quality metal is also used in manufacturing kitchen cabinets. Arch Kitchen uses only fine grade metal for its hardware such as, hinges, doorknobs, handles and screws. Strong metal can easily withstand pressure and will not bend or twist over time.

Whether for your first home, summer home, or dream home, our talented team can really help you. At Designix Inc., we have the products you’re looking for to create the home you’ve always wanted.

We are the manufacturers, providing you over 300 door styles to choose from. Combined with your choice of wood, stains and finishes, the possibilities are endless. From the simple to the more complex, no job is too large or too small, and we have solutions for ALL budgets.

profile:
Robert Cameron is a Toronto based designer specializing in custom interiors and statement wine cellars.  His cellars push the boundaries of design and incorporate the latest technology.  For his interiors, Robert designs furniture, rugs, artwork and anything else required in achieving the best results for each project.

?

Robert is a certified Sommelier with the International Sommelier Guild and offers his clients a wine stocking service as part of his turnkey cellars.  He has worked in the wine industry in Canada, Australia, and France and has traveled to over 25 wine producing countries.  While living in Bordeaux, he achieved an MBA in Wine and Spirits Marketing at the Bordeaux International Wine Institute.
